[---]
title = _("Features")
subhead = _("Do Not Track")
[---] text/html
{% extends "templates/about-features.html" %}
{% block content %}
<div class="col0">

    <p><a href="http://donottrack.us/">&ldquo;Do Not Track&rdquo;</a> (DNT) is a web
    technology that is used to specify if a user wants to be tracked by
    websites such as analytics services, advertising networks, and social
    platforms.  </p>

    <p>Gratipay supports DNT. Enabling your browser's DNT settings ensures
    that Gratipay will disable any use of third-party analytics services.  </p>

    <p>You can read more about how we use DNT headers in our <a
        href="/about/privacy/#dnt">Privacy Policy</a>, and you can find how to
    configure your DNT settings by following one of these links: </p>

    {% set pages = [
    ('https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/how-do-i-turn-do-not-track-feature#w_how-do-i-turn-the-do-not-track-feature-on_2', 'Firefox'),
    ('http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/internet-explorer/use-tracking-protection#ie=ie-11', 'IE'),
    ('http://donottrack.us/images/safari_dnt.png', 'Safari'),
    ('https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/114836', 'Chrome'),
    ('http://www.opera.com/help/tutorials/security/control/#referrer', 'Opera'),
    ('https://support.twitter.com/articles/20169453-twitter-supports-do-not-track', 'Twitter'),
    ('https://en.gravatar.com/support/gravatar-locations/', 'Gravatar')
    ] %}
    {% for page in pages %}
        <a href="{{ page[0] }}">{{ page[1] }}</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    {% endfor %}

</div>
{% endblock %}
